          <p className="text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed"><strong className="text-white">Pro tip for step 2:</strong> The best questions to build content around are not the ones with the highest search volume. They are the ones with the highest intent-to-action ratio. A question like &quot;what is content marketing&quot; has massive volume but low intent. A question like &quot;how to create a content calendar for a 3-person team with no designer&quot; has lower volume but the person asking it is ready to implement a solution immediately. Target high-intent micro-questions for faster ROI.</p>
